post_text:
Note from Mrs. Rumbaugh:

ICMS families,
Due to potentially hazardous weather conditions for Monday, May 20th, ICMS will be closed and all activities cancelled. Our primary reason for canceling is the safety of our students and ICMS families. The National Weather Service says the highest risk for severe weather is tomorrow afternoon when families are on the road during after-school pick up. Also, we have been notified that Boys & Girls Club will be closed tomorrow.
Also, a reminder that Tuesday is the last day for after-school activities and Thursday, our last day of school, we are dismissing at noon. Please make arrangements for those days.
Again, school is closed tomorrow, Monday, May 20th. Please stay safe and weather aware.

post_text:
ICMS Friends and Family,

We would like your help in marketing our school to prospective 6th graders for the upcoming school year. We have come to that critical time of year where parents are making decisions regarding their childrenâ€™s education, and we would like an opportunity to show them what ICMS has to offer.

On February 7th at 6:00 p.m. we will be hosting an open house at our school and would love any interested 5th grade parents to attend. Additionally, we are currently accepting applications for the 2017-18 school year. Details can be found online or parents can pick up applications in person. The deadline for applications is March 1, 2017, with the lottery being held March 6.

Please help us get the word out by sharing this post. You will always be our best marketing strategy. Thank you.

post_text:
Come join us in the 3rd Annual PATRIOT DASH to be held Sunday, October 2, 2016. The PATRIOT DASH is a run/walk at Hefner Lake raising funds for Independence Charter Middle School sports programs, as well as for the physical education/heath programs in order to promote the importance of health and fitness among our school community. Not only is this a great running/walking event capturing beautiful views along Lake Hefner, but it will be a great community event to be enjoyed by everyone!! Sign-up today!!
(https://patriotdash.net/registration)

post_text:
ALL students will be involved in a "Career Shadow Day" on Monday, November 16th. The students will be required to shadow a parent or another adult in a field that interests the student as a career. This will be a part of our Character Education program. The attached form must be completed to receive credit for this activity. If a student does not participate and/or fill out the form, it will count as a "zero" from class for that day. The students will be involved in activities after this experience within their Character Education classes. This is a great way for our students to experience the "outside world." Please make a great experience from this opportunity.

Students need to call and make arrangements before they go to a place to shadow. Students can NOT shadow a teacher in the OKCPS District. We have received calls in the past asking that students not come to the schools. (Too much of a disruption to their classrooms.) Please make sure you adhere to this request.

NO CLASSES November 16th!

ICMS Daily Schedule

The building opens at 7:00 each morning. Free breakfast for everyoneâ€¦ everyday is from 7:15 - 7:40 a.m.

We begin the Morning Assembly at 7:45 a.m. each day. Students need to be in the building ready to begin on time.

6th grade at 2:30 through the West door
7th grade at 2:45 through the Gym doors (south end of building)

post_text:
Penny Wars

Penny Wars is a competition between the 6th, 7th and 8th grades. The class with the highest balance at the end of the week will win a pizza party. Here is how it works: PENNIES will count towards your grade level total. SILVER COINS AND BILLS will count against your grade level total. So, if you want your grade to win, put pennies in your own jar and silver coins and bills in the other grade level jars.

post_text: As you may know, the ICMS website has been unavailable for some time. During that time, we have changed hosting companies and now have a new website that is up and ready to view at http://www.icmsokc.com/.
